# C++ ImageEncryption - Doxygen Documentation

This project includes Doxygen documentation. To generate HTML documentation:

```bash
# Install Doxygen
sudo apt-get install doxygen graphviz  # Ubuntu/Debian
brew install doxygen graphviz          # macOS

# Generate documentation
doxygen Doxyfile

# Open in browser
open docs/html/index.html
```

## Documentation Structure

- `include/` - Header files with API documentation
- `src/` - Implementation with inline comments
- `docs/` - Generated by Doxygen

## API Documentation

### Main Classes

- `ImageEncryption` - Main encryption/decryption class
- `LogisticChaoticMap` - Chaotic map implementation
- `Utils` - Utility functions

### Key Functions

- `ImageEncryption::encryptImage()` - Encrypt image file
- `ImageEncryption::decryptImage()` - Decrypt image file
- `LogisticChaoticMap::getPermutation()` - Generate pixel permutation

## Building Documentation

The documentation is automatically generated from inline comments in the source code.
All public functions and classes have comprehensive documentation using Doxygen format.

```cpp
/**
 * @brief Brief description
 * @param param Parameter description
 * @return Return value description
 * @throws std::exception Exception description
 */
void myFunction(int param);
```

## Online Documentation

Generate and host documentation:

```bash
# Generate and copy to gh-pages
doxygen Doxyfile
cp -r docs/html/* ../gh-pages/

# Push to GitHub
cd ../gh-pages
git add .
git commit -m "Update documentation"
git push origin gh-pages
```
